		<h3>Introduction</h3>
		<br/>

		<p>This page list the Snowmix Guides. The Snowmix Guides are manuals each
		centered on a specific topic with detailed examples on how to use a
		specific group of features within Snowmix.</p>

		<p>For now the following Snowmix Guides has been written:</p>

		<ul>
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/Audio/">Snowmix Audio Guide</a>.
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/AV%20Sync/">Snowmix AV Sync Guide</a>.
			<li><a href="[HOME]Examples/scripting.html">Snowmix Basic Scripting Guide</a>.
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/Snowmix%20Libraries/">Snowmix Libraries Guide</a>.
			<li><a href="[HOME]Documentation/guide-glshapes.html">Snowmix Glshapes Guide</a>. Snowmix OpenGL Support.
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/Snowmix%20Tutorials%20-%20Scenes/">Snowmix Scenes Tutorial</a>.
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/Shapes/">Snowmix Shapes Guide</a>.
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/Tcl%20Interpreter/">Snowmix Tcl Interpreter Guide</a>.
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/Video%20Text">Snowmix Text Guide</a>.
			<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/snowmix/wiki/Snowmix%20and%20CDNs/">Feeding Live Video to CDNs</a>.
		</ul>

		<p>There will be written more manuals and the existing ones are expected to be updated and improved over time.</p>

